Here's the XAML and ViewModel setup:

### XAML

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="Auto,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}"
                           WidthRequest="48" HeightRequest="48" />
                    <VerticalStackLayout Grid.Column="1" VerticalOptions="Center" Spacing="4">
                        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontAttributes="Bold" />
                        <Label Text="{Binding Description}" TextColor="Gray" />
                    </VerticalStackLayout>
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

### ViewModel

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    // Pull-to-refresh: reload from API, then set IsRefreshing = false
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
        Items = new ObservableCollection<Item>(data);
        IsRefreshing = false;
    }

    // Selection: navigate to detail, then clear selection
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;
        await _nav.GoToAsync("DetailPage", new Dictionary<string, object>
        {
            { "Item", CurrentItem }
        });
        CurrentItem = null; // reset so the same item can be re-selected
    }
}
```

### Key binding relationships

| XAML Property | ViewModel Property | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `IsRefreshing` | `IsRefreshing` (bool, TwoWay) | Shows/hides spinner; **you must set it to `false`** when done |
| `Command` (RefreshView) | `RefreshCommand` | Triggers API reload |
| `SelectedItem` | `CurrentItem` (TwoWay) | Tracks the selected item |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires navigation on tap |
| `ItemsSource` | `Items` (ObservableCollection) | The data — use `ObservableCollection<T>`, never `List<T>` |

### Important notes

- **Reset `CurrentItem` to `null`** after navigation so the user can re-select the same item.
- **Set `IsRefreshing = false`** at the end of your refresh command or the spinner spins forever.
- Use `x:DataType` on the `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings.
- Never use `ViewCell` inside a `CollectionView` template — use `Grid`, `StackLayout`, etc.
